    en: "New York General Business Law Article 35-D (the Pet Dealer Consumer Protection Act, often called the Puppy Lemon Law) gives the buyer of a dog or cat from a pet dealer specific remedies if the animal becomes ill within 14 days or is diagnosed with a congenital or hereditary defect within 180 days. Remedies include refund, replacement, or reimbursement for veterinary bills. The law applies to pet dealers (stores and breeders selling 9+ animals per year) — not to private sellers or shelters."
